description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PARTNERS IN HEALTH&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12 Month Salaried GP Contract with view to extending/Partnership&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We want to keep and protect the best of general practice, while seizing new opportunities with both hands&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Practice &lt;/strong&gt;is playing an active part in the development of Gloucester Inner City Primary Care Network with a particular interest in health inequalities&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our GPs&lt;/strong&gt; are developing their role as primary care consultants, managing individualised continuous care for our patients with complex medical needs&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our nurses&lt;/strong&gt; manage urgent care, chronic disease, minor illness&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mental health nurse&lt;/strong&gt; is available for patients to book appointments directly from reception&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our admin team&lt;/strong&gt; read our letters, highlight actions, and forward medication changes to our &lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;practice pharmacists &lt;/strong&gt;who independently resolve the majority of medication queries&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a training practice, we facilitate a culture of learningfor all staff and actively encourage extended roles such as MSK, joint injections, minor surgery and dermatology within a supportive work environment. Portfolio careers are supported. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We&lt;strong&gt; prioritise&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access for the acutely unwell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;prescribing nurses triage all same day appointment requests and manage minor illness independently&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Continuity for our complex patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;named GP has 15 minute appointments and phone slots for their own patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;seeing patients face to face where appropriate while maintaining staff safety&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MDT working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;time at the end of the morning to follow up with other clinicians, and links with local community services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking after each other&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;coffee, open door culture of asking for help when needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact us to talk about the details we haven’t included in this ad and find out more:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Teresa Pietroni&lt;/strong&gt;, GP Partner &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;t.pietroni@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lesley Harris&lt;/strong&gt;, Practice Director &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;lesley.harris12@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Partners in Health, Pavilion Family Doctors&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;153a Stroud Road, Gloucester, GL1 5JJ. Tel: 01452 385555&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
